@startuml signal_flow_integrated_warning_network
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam ParticipantPadding 18
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam NoteBorderColor #808080
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title Level 3: Integrated Warning Signal Flow\n(Domain Context → V2X → ADAS → CGW → Render / Verification)

box "Ingress Source" #F7F7F7
participant "Emergency Source /\nValidation Stimulus" as SRC #FFFFFF
end box

box "Domain Context" #F7F7F7
participant "Context Owners\nVCU / MDPS / NAV-IVI" as CTX #FFFFFF
end box

box "Backbone / Decision / Boundary" #F2F2F2
participant "ETH Backbone" as ETHB #FFFFFF
participant "V2X" as V2X #FFFFFF
participant "ADAS" as ADAS #FFFFFF
participant "CGW" as CGW #FFFFFF
end box

box "Render / Observation" #F7F7F7
participant "BCM / CLU /\nHUD / AMP" as RENDER #FFFFFF
participant "TEST_BAS /\nSGW / DCM / EXT_DIAG" as OBS #FFFFFF
end box

== 1. Domain context publication ==

CTX -> CGW : frmVehicleStateCanMsg (0x2A0)\nfrmSteeringStateCanMsg (0x100)\nfrmNavigationRouteMsg (0x285)

note right of CGW
    **Local CAN Context**
    • Chassis / powertrain state
    • Steering activity
    • Zone / route / speed-limit context
    **Cycle**: 100ms
    **Network**: 11-bit CAN
end note

CTX -> ETHB : ethVehicleStateMsg (0x510)\nethSteeringMsg (0x511)\nethNavContextMsg (0x512)
ETHB -> CGW : backbone context delivery

note right of ETHB
    **Backbone Context Publication**
    • 0x510 ~ 0x512
    • cross-domain shared context
    **Cycle**: 100ms
    **Network**: UDP multicast
end note

== 2. Emergency ingress and acceptance ==

SRC -> ETHB : ETH_EmergencyAlert (0xE100)\nemergencyType / direction / ETA / sourceId / alertState
ETHB -> V2X : emergency ingress delivery

note right of V2X
    **Message**: ETH_EmergencyAlert (0xE100)
    **Signals**:
    • emergencyType
    • emergencyDirection
    • eta
    • sourceId
    • alertState
    **Cycle**: 100ms
    **Network**: UDP multicast
end note

note left of SRC
    **Ingress Interpretation**
    • product meaning owner = V2X
    • TEST_SCN may emit the same frame
      as validation stimulus only
end note

== 3. Emergency normalization by V2X ==

activate V2X
V2X -> V2X : Compare active candidates\npriority = emergencyType > ETA > sourceId
V2X -> V2X : Update Core::emergencyContext\nand CoreState::emergencyIngress*
V2X -> ETHB : ETH_EmergencyMonitor (0x1C2)\nemergencyContext / timeoutClear
ETHB -> OBS : emergency monitor observation
V2X -> ADAS : CoreState::emergencyIngress*
deactivate V2X

note right of V2X
    **V2X Owner Rule**
    • normalize emergency ingress
    • own timeout clear heartbeat
    • publish ingress metadata for product consumers
end note

== 4. Risk calculation and arbitration by ADAS ==

activate ADAS
ADAS -> ADAS : Compute R_emg\n0.55*etaScore + speedScore + directionScore + typeBias
ADAS -> ADAS : Compute TTC and R_obj\nfrom object range / relative speed / confidence
ADAS -> ADAS : Select selectedAlertDecision*\nand decelAssistDecisionReq
ADAS -> CGW : selectedAlertDecision*\ndecelAssistDecisionReq
ADAS -> ETHB : ethSelectedAlertMsg (0xE200)\nethEmergencyRiskMsg (0xE210)\nethDecelAssistReqMsg (0xE211)
ETHB -> OBS : selected alert / risk / decel observation
deactivate ADAS

note right of ADAS
    **Decision Contract**
    • emergency risk + object risk
    • selected alert before gateway shaping
    • decel assist decision request
    **Trigger**: Event + 50ms / 100ms
    **Network**: local runtime + UDP evidence seam
end note

== 5. Boundary shaping by CGW ==

activate CGW
CGW -> CGW : Evaluate boundaryAlive\nwarningPathStatus / e2eHealthState / failSafeMode
CGW -> CGW : Apply timeout clear and fallback alert\nshape selectedAlertEffective*
CGW -> RENDER : selectedAlertEffective*\nwarningPathStatus / failSafeMode
CGW -> ETHB : ethFailSafeStateMsg (0xE212)\nethObjectSafetyStateMsg (0xE216)
ETHB -> OBS : fail-safe / object-safety observation
deactivate CGW

note right of CGW
    **Boundary Rule B01**
    • stale / timeout clear authority
    • fail-safe authority
    • effective warning state publication
    **Cycle**: 100ms + Event
    **Network**: local seam + UDP monitor
end note

== 6. Render feedback and observer aggregation ==

activate RENDER
RENDER -> RENDER : Update ambient / cluster /\nHUD / audio output state
deactivate RENDER

activate OBS
OBS -> OBS : Aggregate Test::base*\nand observe Diag::* semantic state
deactivate OBS

note over V2X, OBS
    **Review Points**
    1. Domain CAN keeps local context ownership
    2. V2X owns emergency normalization
    3. ADAS owns warning / risk arbitration
    4. CGW owns timeout clear and fail-safe shaping
    5. TEST_BAS / DIAG observe after product meaning is published
end note

== 7. Continuous monitoring and timeout clear ==

loop Every 100ms
    CTX -> ETHB : context refresh
    ETHB -> CGW : context delivery
    SRC -> ETHB : emergency refresh if active
    ETHB -> V2X : emergency delivery
    V2X -> ETHB : emergency monitor refresh
end

SRC -> ETHB : Emergency refresh stops
activate V2X
V2X -> V2X : 1000ms watchdog expiry\nset timeoutClear = 1
V2X -> CGW : emergencyContext clear / timeoutClear pulse
deactivate V2X

activate CGW
CGW -> CGW : Raise fallback alert if boundary path\nstill requires degraded warning
CGW -> RENDER : selectedAlertEffective* update\nor clear transition
deactivate CGW

note over V2X, RENDER
    **Timeout / Recovery Rule**
    • V2X decides timeout clear pulse
    • CGW decides final degraded / fail-safe shaping
    • render and observer nodes consume published result only
end note

@enduml
